🚀 Step 1: App me OTEL SDK add karo
Apne microservice / app me OpenTelemetry SDK add karo
Har request ke liye span / trace generate hota hai
env:
  - name: OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
    value: "http://otel-collector:4317"
Matlab: app bata raha hai “bhai traces OTEL Collector ko bhej do”
🚀 Step 2: OTEL Collector EKS me deploy karo
Collector ka kaam = receive traces → forward to backend (Tempo)
helm repo add open-telemetry https://open-telemetry.github.io/opentelemetry-helm-charts
helm repo update
helm install otel-collector open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector --set mode=daemonset
Collector config snippet:
receivers:
  otlp:
    protocols:
      grpc:
      http:

exporters:
  tempo:
    endpoint: "tempo.tempo.svc.cluster.local:4317"

service:
  pipelines:
    traces:
      receivers: [otlp]
      exporters: [tempo]
Receiver → kahan se traces aayenge
Exporter → kahan bhejna hai (Tempo)
Pipeline → receiver → exporter ka connection
🚀 Step 3: Deploy Tempo + Grafana
Tempo = traces ka storage
Grafana → add Tempo datasource
Dashboard me service maps, latency, error traces dekh sakte ho
🚀 Step 4: Dashboard me traces dekho
Service map → kaunsa service slow hai
Latency histogram → request kitni der me complete hui
Error traces → kaunsa request fail hua
Optional: metrics nikal ke Prometheus me bhej do → alerts
🚀 Step 5: End-to-end Flow
User Request → App Pod (OTEL SDK) → OTEL Collector → Tempo → Grafana Dashboard
Traces visualize → bottlenecks + slow requests
Metrics & alerts → optional, Prometheus + Grafana
🧠 Interview Hinglish line

“EKS me app ko OpenTelemetry SDK se instrument karte hain, jo traces generate karta hai. Ye traces OTEL Collector ko jaate hain, wahan se Grafana Tempo me store hote hain aur Grafana dashboard me service map, latency aur errors dikhte hain. Metrics derive karke alerts bhi set kar sakte hain.”
